	<text xml:lang="la">
		<body>
			<div xml:id="div1" corresp="regest1">
				<p>
					<s n="1" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Salve, doctissime <persName ref="p495" type="citizen_name" cert="high">Bullingere</persName>.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="2" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Militum turba tum et equitum<note xml:id="fn1" type="footnote" n="1">Zur Anwerbung von Soldaten im Zusammenhang mit den Spannungen um <placeName type="citizen_name" ref="l306" cert="high">Mailand</placeName> vgl. oben <ref target="file10858">Nr. 819</ref>, 1-8, und unten <ref target="file10870">Nr. 831</ref>f. Zum Aufbruch von Truppen aus dem <placeName cert="high" type="citizen_name" ref="l6">Allgäu</placeName> unter Hauptmann <persName ref="p7480" cert="high">Kaspar von Frundsberg</persName> vgl. Nikolaus Ellenbog, Briefwechsel, hg. v. Andreas Bigelmair und Friedrich Zoepfl, Münster in Westfalen 1938. -Corpus Catholicorum 19/21, S. 374, 30-32.</note> hominum piorum scilicet, ita obrutus et districtus, ut vix respirare liceat, tantum abest ut tibi, que velim et cupiam, scribere queam.</s>
					<s n="3" xml:lang="la" type="auto" ana="salute">Tu itaque hoc meum salvere et silere boni consule, vir integritate et eruditione excellentissime.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="4" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Que tua ex officina prodierunt interim, cura ut cum hoc <persName type="citizen_name">Petro</persName><note xml:id="fn2" type="footnote" n="2">Ein <persName type="citizen_name">Peter</persName> [...] ist bereits im Brief vom 14. Nov. 1535 als Bote genannt (vgl. <bibl>HBBW V</bibl> <ref target="file10715">[Nr. 677]</ref>, S. 425, 13).</note> nunc cognito tibi accipiam ac aliorum tuorum symmistarum.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="5" xml:lang="la" type="auto" ana="farewell">Vale, et Christus in te pergat peragere, quod cepit in suam laudem et gloriam et suę ecclesię profectum et ornamentum.</s>
					<s n="6" xml:lang="la" type="auto" ana="farewell">Vale cum tuis omnibus et ecclesia tua sancta.</s>
					<s n="7" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Vicissim per te oramus.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="8" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Ipsa<note xml:id="fna" type="footnote" n="a"><hi>vor</hi> ipsa <hi>gestrichenes</hi> isp.</note> ascensionis die anno etc. 36.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="9" xml:lang="la" type="auto"><persName type="citizen_name" ref="p330" cert="high">Barptolomaeus</persName><note xml:id="fnb" type="footnote" n="b"><hi>nach</hi> <persName type="citizen_name" ref="p330" cert="high">Barptolomaeus</persName> <hi>von späterer Hand</hi> <persName ref="p330" cert="high">Bertlin</persName>.</note>, tuus discipulus.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<note type="address">[Adresse auf der Rückseite:]</note>
					<s n="10" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Viro pietate et doctrina prestantissimo <persName ref="p495" type="citizen_name" cert="high">Heinricho Bullingero</persName>, ecclesię <placeName ref="l587" type="auto_name" cert="high">Tigurinę</placeName> episcopo laudatissimo, suo preceptori cum primis honorando.</s>
				</p>
			</div>
